iwd is [[Article description::an up-and-coming wireless daemon for Linux.]] It is written by Intel and aims to replace wpa_supplicant.

iwd has NOT been added to the Gentoo ebuild repository (yet).

== Installation ==

=== Manual ===

{{Warning|iwd is a work in process is now definitely not ready for prime time computing!}}

iwd can be manually compiled and installed by following the [https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/network/wireless/iwd.git/about/ upstream directions].

